There has been no multitrillion-dollar spending bill to combat these and other domestic emergencies.
When Congress passes a spending bill that is fully “paid for,” it sends two sets of instructions to the Federal Reserve.
Instead of writing a bill that would send two sets of instructions to the Fed, Congress is pushing through a $2 trillion spending bill that will send just one set of instructions.
Spending or not spending money is always a political choice.
